snippet.textDisplay: The softness of Rahat's voice robbed the song of that 'sense of rebellion against helplessness' that you find in the original song sung by Ali Azmat. Probably Noor alone would have done a better job since he belongs to the same genre and Rahat is just the opposite. I enjoyed the Jam at the end though but overall an experimentation gone terribly awry!

Probably Noor alone would have done a better job since he belongs to the same genre and Rahat is just the opposite. I enjoyed the Jam at the end though but overall an experimentation gone terribly awry!
